               <head>Shifa'i's medical treatise</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Khulāṣah-'i Shifāʾī by Shifāʾī, Muẓaffar ibn Muḥammad, -1555 or 1556</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85083158 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85068424" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Or_16269-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>A rare medical treatise in two books, comprising respectively three maṭlabs and two fanns, as well as a preface (dībācha). By Muẓaffar ibn Muḥammad al-Ḥusaynī al-Kāshānī, called
                al-Shifā’ī (d. 963/1556), who is best known as the author of Qarābādīn-i Shifā’ī (or Ṭibb-i Shifā’ī).</p>
                        <p>Munzavī, in FNKhF I, pp. 529-30, cites three copies in Iran and three in Iraq; Storey, PL II/2 E, pp. 245-6, mentions only one in Najaf and one in St. Petersburg.</p>
                        <p>The present manuscript contains some apparent inaccuracies, such as the omission of az before ḥikmat in the opening passage (see below). It is incomplete at the end.</p>
                        <p>Begins: Basmala Ḥamd-i bīnihāyat va sanā-yi bīghāyat Ḥakīmī-rā ki ḥikmat-i kāmila ān mizāj-rā az amzāj-i javāhir-i ‘anāṣir-i mukhtalifat al-āsār iḥdās namūd</p>
                        <p>Ends: va nabāt khwurand va nabāt va sharāb banafsha va khashkhāsh laq (??) kunand va ghazā khw[urand]</p>
                        <p>Undated: probably 13th/19th century.</p>
                        <p>Nasta‘līq. 17 lines. European wove paper. Red headings. 234 folios. 178 x 112 mm.; text area 150 x 53 mm. Black leather binding with blind impressed medallions, rebacked.</p>
                        <p>Purchased from A al-Shakri, 20 January 2006</p>
                     </note>
